@Franqsanz 

What you need to do is stop the test execution loop when the first test fails and the new mode is active. The loop is located in runner::call_test_functions. The part of the code responsible for running the tests is in runner::run_test, where it's determined if the test has passed or not.

To make it simpler, I recommend that if a test fails with the stop on fail mode active, print a message on the screen indicating that the test execution has been stopped due to a failed test. Then stop the test execution (exit 1)

